    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-10-20T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-10-20T21:00:00-05:00" n="935"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d935">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.0221/10–2154: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 935<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d935fn1">Repeated to Vienna eyes only for the
                        Ambassador.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-10-21T03:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 21, 1954—3 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 3. Eyes only Acting Secretary from
                    Secretary. In meeting at residence following Four-Power meeting<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d935fn2">Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> was
                        in Paris to attend the Four-Power, Nine-Power, and North Atlantic Council
                        Ministerial meetings which took place from Oct. 20 through 23.</note> I
                    raised with <persName corresp="#p_EASA1">Eden</persName> possibility
                    redeployment in Austria some or all UK troops now in Trieste. I told him I
                    wished to speak further with him on this matter after I had had opportunity to
                    talk with <persName corresp="#p_GLGAM1">Gruenther</persName>. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EASA1">Eden</persName> promised consider matter with his
                    advisers, but his reaction at first blush was that in absence any organized
                    units in UK, pressures <pb facs="0777" n="1977" xml:id="pg_1977"/> would be
                    extremely strong to bring all forces now in Trieste back to England.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
